  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM3.4.9">
<l>piṟaitaṅku caṭaiyāṉai valattē vaittup piramaṉaitta ṉuntiyilē tōṟṟu vittu</l>
<l>kaṟaitaṅku vēltaṭaṅkaṇ tiruvai mārpil kalantavaṉṟā ḷaṇaikiṟpīr kaḻunīr kūṭit</l>
<l>tuṟaitaṅku kamalattut tuyiṉṟu kaitait tōṭārum poticōṟṟuc cuṇṇam naṇṇi</l>
<l>ciṟaivaṇṭu kaḷipāṭum vayalcūḻ kāḻic cīrāma viṇṇakarē cērmi ṉīrē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>You who would clasp the feet of him who is intimate with Tiru on his chest,</l>
<l rend="indent">her wide eyes like a spear with blood remaining,</l>
<l>Keeping at his right, the one in whose locks the crescent moon remains,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] producing Brahmā in his navel,</l>
<l>Gather you [all] at Cīrāmaviṇṇakaram in Kāḻi surrounded by fields</l>
<l rend="indent">where a winged bee sings happily, having arrived at a waterlily,</l>
<l>[Then] dozed in a lotus which remained along the shore, [and] rested in pollen</l>
<l rend="indent">spread upon the petals, from a stamen of a screw pine bud.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
